Ryanair chief executive Michael O'Leary took aim at Air France in interview with French newspaper . 
  He said he despises the 'French political class', but loves France and the French . 
  Ryanair will slash fares by as much as 15 per cent over the next two years . 
  Mr O’Leary said the average fare could be as low as €40 (approximately £26) He attributed the fare cuts to lower oil prices and said the airline will pass the savings on to customers . 
 